      "rationale": "Use error is scoped out because the CFD analysis is performed exclusively by the original model development team under a controlled simulation protocol with mandatory peer review of all case setups and post-processing scripts. The device decision supported by this model is a comparative ranking of operating conditions, not an absolute performance certification; consequently, user-induced systematic errors that affect all cases equally do not alter the rank ordering that constitutes the decision output. At MRL 2 with MEDIUM model influence, ASME V&V 40 Table 3 does not mandate a standalone use-error assessment when procedural controls are documented."
